16/03/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The High Court convicted two former Croatian Serb soldiers Monday (March 15th) of war crimes against civilians during the 1991-1995 war in Croatia.
Pane Bulat was sentenced to 15 years in prison and Rade Vranesevic got 12 years for killing five elderly women and one man in Banski Kovacevac in 1992.
(Beta, RTS, B92, AP - 15/03/10)
